---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
	title="Privacy Policy - Attendance Tracker"
	description="Our privacy policy explains how we handle your data. Spoiler: We don't sell it, and we keep it minimal."
>
	<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-s-md py-s-4xl md:py-s-section">
		<h1 class="display-lg mb-s-xl tracking-tighter">Privacy Policy</h1>
		
		<div class="space-y-s-xl body-sm text-body leading-relaxed">
			<section>
				<h2 class="body-md font-semibold text-ink mb-s-sm">1. Information We Collect</h2>
				<p>We collect minimal information required to provide our services. This includes your subject names and attendance logs which are stored locally on your device unless you choose to sync with an account.</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="body-md font-semibold text-ink mb-s-sm">2. How We Use Data</h2>
				<p>Your data is used solely to calculate your attendance percentages and bunking predictions. We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties.</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="body-md font-semibold text-ink mb-s-sm">3. Local Storage</h2>
				<p>By default, Attendance Tracker uses your browser's Local Storage to save your data. This means your data stays on your machine and is never sent to our servers unless you explicitly sign up for a cloud account.</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="body-md font-semibold text-ink mb-s-sm">4. Cookies</h2>
				<p>We use essential cookies to maintain your session and remember your theme preferences (Light/Dark mode).</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="body-md font-semibold text-ink mb-s-sm">5. Contact Us</h2>
				<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please reach out via our contact page.</p>
			</section>

			<p class="caption text-mute mt-s-4xl">Last updated: May 30, 2026</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
